  ],
  "text": "In the Firefox NSS library under security/nss/lib/ssl/ (repo: firefox--871325b8), the following five files implement core TLS/SSL protocol handling:\n\n1. ssl3con.c — Implements SSL 3.0/TLS record processing and cipher suite negotiation. The primary entry point for record-layer processing is ssl3_HandleRecord(), which dispatches incoming SSL/TLS records. It also contains ssl3_HandleHandshakeMessage(), ssl3_HandleClientHello(), ssl3_HandleServerHello(), and ssl3_SendRecord() for the full SSL3/TLS handshake and record lifecycle.\n\n2. tls13con.c — Implements TLS 1.3 handshake and record processing. The primary post-hello handshake dispatcher is tls13_HandlePostHelloHandshakeMessage(). It also contains tls13_HandleClientHelloPart2(), tls13_HandleServerHelloPart2(), and the full TLS 1.3 key schedule and handshake state machine.\n\n3. dtlscon.c — Implements DTLS-specific protocol handling, including datagram reassembly, retransmission timers, and message sequencing. The primary handshake handler is dtls_HandleHandshake(), with dtls_HandleHandshakeMessage() for individual message dispatch and DTLS_GetHandshakeTimeout() for timer management.\n\n4. ssl3ecc.c — Implements ECC (Elliptic Curve Cryptography) cipher suite operations, originally split out from ssl3con.c. Key functions include ssl_NamedGroup2ECParams() for EC parameter encoding, ssl3_HandleECDHServerKeyExchange() and ssl3_HandleECDHClientKeyExchange() for ECDH key exchange handling, and ssl3_SendECDHClientKeyExchange() for sending ECDH key material.\n\n5. sslexp.h — The header file declaring experimental SSL APIs. It defines the SSL_EXPERIMENTAL_API macro and SSL_DEPRECATED_EXPERIMENTAL_API macro, which provide a safe dispatch mechanism for experimental NSS SSL functions (such as SSL_GetExtensionSupport, SSL_InstallExtensionHooks, SSL_SetupAntiReplay, etc.) that are not guaranteed to remain stable across NSS versions."
}

